org.cicirello.sequences

Class PrimitiveValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cicirello.sequences.PrimitiveValue

  • public final class PrimitiveValue
extends java.lang.Object
    The PrimitiveValue class is a wrapper class for all eight of Java's primitive types. In some simple sense it is similar to the existing wrapper classes from the Java API. However, it has some key differences. First, one class that can be used with any primitive type value, unlike the set of wrapper classes in the Java API. Second, although in the Java API, the six number types have wrappers that share a superclass ( Number ), the wrappers for the boolean and char types are not in that hierarchy. The only ancestor class that all eight of Java's wrapper classes have in common is the Object class. Third, the PrimitiveValue class otherwise has much less functionality. It has been implemented to support specific methods of the PrimitiveSequence class, specifically the PrimitiveSequence.get method, and the PrimitiveSequence.set method.
    Since:
    1.1
